<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF8FFF9CFF7EFE84FDF6FCA0" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF7EFE84FD83FD88" blockId="14.[136,1452,337,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF7EFE84FEEBFE8B" bold="true" box="[136,284,337,363]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Lingulate leaves unknown; expanded submerged or floating leaves unknown; leaves of terrestrial plants spathulate, up to 6.0 mm long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFBA6FEA3FB5FFE70" box="[1104,1192,374,400]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
wide; secondary veins do not rejoin the central vein, toward the centre of the blade small veins may arise from the primary vein, these may be free or join the secondary veins, petiole 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFD87FE6BFD0EFE38" box="[625,761,446,472]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.7 mm</quantity>
long. Flowers pedunculate, 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF8FFF9CFBCFFE6BFBB9FE38" box="[1081,1102,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF8FFF9CFB70FE6BFB6CFE38" box="[1158,1179,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
in the same axil. Bracts probably lacking. Styles divergent or erect, 0.4–0.5 µm long. Filament arising from peduncle, slightly curved, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFAA1FE37FF43FDC0" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.6 mm</quantity>
long; anthers quadrilocular, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFE0BFDD3FD63FDC0" box="[509,660,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="0.185" valueMax="0.27" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.27 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFD06FDD3FC8EFDC0" box="[752,889,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
wide; pollen yellow. Fruit subsessile, wider than high, maroon or chestnut when mature, 0.8–1.0 mm long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFCEAFDFFFC86FDA4" box="[796,881,554,580]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
wide, broadly winged throughout except for a very narrow part where mericarps are connected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF4BFDA4FAC5FD6C" blockId="14.[136,1452,337,1156]" box="[189,1330,625,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF4BFDA4FEAEFD6B" bold="true" box="[189,345,625,651]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Illustrations:</emphasis>
—Plates 2(M) and 3(3–4) in 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF8FFF9CFD6BFDA7FC8FFD6D" author="Schotsman, H. D." box="[669,888,626,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" pagination="357 - 375" refId="ref35721" refString="Schotsman, H. D. (1985 c) Biologie floral des Callitriche (Callitrichaceae). II: Etude sur quelques especes d'Oceanie. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, section B 7 (4): 357 - 375." type="journal article" year="1985">Schotsman (1985c)</bibRefCitation>
, plate 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFC34FDA7FC1AFD6C" box="[962,1005,626,652]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF8FFF9CFC05FDA7FB27FD6D" author="Schotsman, H. D." box="[1011,1232,626,653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" pagination="115 - 121" refId="ref35765" refString="Schotsman, H. D. (1985 d) Une nouvelle espece de Callitriche (Callitrichaceae) de Papoua-Nouvelle-Giunee: C. cycloptera Schotsm. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, section B 7 (2): 115 - 121." type="journal article" year="1985">Schotsman (1985d)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF8FFF9CFB2AFDA7FAD9FD6C" box="[1244,1326,626,652]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,225,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-31@4.[151,1436,190,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. antarctica, b—C. aucklandica, c—C. brachycarpa, d—C. brutia, e—C. capricorni, f—C. chathamensis, g—C. cyclocarpa i face on and ii end on, h—C. cycloptera, i—C. deflexa, j—C. fuliginea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577540/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Fig. 1h</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF4BFD40FDF6FCA0" blockId="14.[136,1452,337,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF4BFD40FEA1FD4F" bold="true" box="[189,342,661,687]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFE84FD43FDFEFD50" authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1985" box="[370,521,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cycloptera">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFE84FD43FDFEFD50" box="[370,521,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">C. cycloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFC6AFD43FB9AFD50" box="[924,1133,662,688]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFC6AFD43FBE2FD50" box="[924,1045,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region by the wing of the fruit which is very broad (approximately ½ the width of fruit) and extends completely around each mericarp except for the narrow point where the mericarps are attached. The maroon/chestnut colour of the fruit also helps to distinguish it from many species. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFD9CFCD7FD1FFCFC" authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1856" box="[618,744,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muelleri">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFD9CFCD7FD1FFCFC" box="[618,744,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">C. muelleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but that species has leaves with a single tooth on each margin which is lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFE95FCF3FE0DFCA0" authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1985" box="[355,506,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cycloptera">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFE95FCF3FE0DFCA0" box="[355,506,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">C. cycloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF8FFF9DFF4BFC9CFBCBFF3D" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="258" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF4BFC9CFF14FC4C" blockId="14.[136,1452,337,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF4BFC9CFEAEFC83" bold="true" box="[189,345,841,867]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFE83FC9FFDF9FC84" authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1985" box="[373,526,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cycloptera">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFE83FC9FFDF9FC84" box="[373,526,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">C. cycloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to New 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF8FFF9CFD0CFC9FFCB9FC84" box="[762,846,842,868]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, where it is known from two areas: Mount Suckling (Goropi), the highest peak in the Goropu Mountains in the south east, and Mount Salawaket on the Huon Peninsula (
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF8FFF9CFF66FC47FF22FC4C" box="[144,213,914,940]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[136,229,1781,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-455@14.[274,1313,1181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. The distribution of confirmed specimens of C. cycloptera" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580491/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF4BFC60FF01FB64" blockId="14.[136,1452,337,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF4BFC60FE39FC30" bold="true" box="[189,462,949,976]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFE1CFC63FD74FC30" authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1985" box="[490,643,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cycloptera">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFE1CFC63FD74FC30" box="[490,643,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">C. cycloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms lawns between mosses and liverworts on peaty soils under the overhanging branches of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFE51FC0EFC56FC14" authority="de Laub. (1969: 334)" authorityName="de Laub." authorityPageNumber="334" authorityYear="1969" box="[423,929,986,1012]" class="Pinopsida" family="Podocarpaceae" genus="Dacrycarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="expansus">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFE51FC0EFD5EFC14" box="[423,681,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Dacrycarpus expansus</emphasis>
de Laub. (1969: 334)
</taxonomicName>
trees on the edge of high-elevation peat bogs dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFEDEFC2BFD23FBF9" authority="Ridl. (1913: 268)" authorityName="Ridl." authorityPageNumber="268" authorityYear="1913" box="[296,724,1022,1049]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Deschampsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klossii">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFEDEFC2BFDFAFBF8" box="[296,525,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Deschampsia klossii</emphasis>
Ridl. (1913: 268)
</taxonomicName>
tussocks in a region which air temperatures may vary from –5 ºC (or even –8 ºC) at night to 22 ºC during the day (J.F.Veldkamp in litt. to H.D.Schotsman) (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF8FFF9CFB92FBF7FA68FBDC" author="Schotsman, H. D." box="[1124,1439,1058,1085]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" pagination="115 - 121" refId="ref35765" refString="Schotsman, H. D. (1985 d) Une nouvelle espece de Callitriche (Callitrichaceae) de Papoua-Nouvelle-Giunee: C. cycloptera Schotsm. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, section B 7 (2): 115 - 121." type="journal article" year="1985">Schotsman 1985d: 119–102</bibRefCitation>
). It has also been found growing among liverworts and mosses in the bed of a dried-out oxbow (
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFB32FB93FB07FB80" box="[1220,1264,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">ibid</emphasis>
.). 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFAF9FB93FA5BFB80" box="[1295,1452,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8625" metricValueMax="2.065" metricValueMin="1.66" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="m" value="1862.5" valueMax="2065.0" valueMin="1660.0">1660–2065 m</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8BA53FFEFF8FFF9CFF7EF920FCDCF8EA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580491" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6580491" box="[136,811,1781,1803]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580491/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" startId="14.[136,229,1781,1803]" targetBox="[280,1305,1188,1747]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF7EF920FCDCF8EA" blockId="14.[136,811,1781,1803]" box="[136,811,1781,1803]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF7EF920FF00F8EA" bold="true" box="[136,247,1781,1803]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">FIGURE 9</emphasis>
. The distribution of confirmed specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF8FFF9CFD5CF923FCDCF8EA" authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1985" box="[682,811,1781,1803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cycloptera">C. cycloptera</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF8FFF9CFF4BF8ECFD58F7CC" blockId="14.[136,1451,1849,2093]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF8FFF9CFF4BF8ECFE4BF8B3" bold="true" box="[189,444,1849,1875]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
—This species is known from a small number of collections from two areas in 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF8FFF9CFA91F8EFFEECF898" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
. It is not known to face any particular threats but it has an estimated Extent of Occurrence (EOO) of 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFF7EF857FEF6F87C" box="[136,257,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4539" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="km" value="14539.0">14,539 km</quantity>
<superScript id="28AFC23EFF8FFF9CFEF7F857FEFEF870" attach="left" box="[257,265,1922,1936]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">2</superScript>
and AOO of 
<quantity id="1822C293FF8FFF9CFE52F857FE1BF87C" box="[420,492,1922,1948]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" unit="km" value="12.0">12 km</quantity>
<superScript id="28AFC23EFF8FFF9CFE1AF857FE03F870" attach="left" box="[492,500,1922,1936]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="257">2</superScript>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF8FFF9CFDF2F857FD78F87C" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[516,655,1922,1948]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" refId="ref32363" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd ed. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK. 32 pp" type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The Pumpunipon Plain is considered to be a single wetland complex on the floodplain of the Pumpinawa River and is therefore treated here as a single location, with the Huon Peninsula as a second location. This species is likely to be vulnerable to climate change as it is restricted to high altitude, while areas where it has been recorded around Mount Suckling are threatened by forest clearance, it is therefore assessed as Vulnerable: B1ab(iii)+2ab(iii); D2 (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF8FFF9CFDEEF7C7FD54F7CC" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[536,675,2066,2092]" pageId="14" pageNumber="257" refId="ref32363" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd ed. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK. 32 pp" type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
